ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The alcoholic tastant of the subject administered during the taste test
Order of Gatorade and alcohol stimuli samples for Block 1
Order of Gatorade and alcohol stimuli samples for Block 2
Rating of flavor intensity for the first alcohol sample
Notes: 2 = Barely Detectable; 6 = Weak; 16 = Moderate; 34 = Strong; 50 = Very Strong; 100 = Strongest Imaginable

ElementDescription: Rating of flavor liking for the first alcohol sample
Notes: 2 = Greatest Imaginable Dislike; 14 = Dislike Extremely; 22 = Dislike Very Much; 32 = Dislike Moderately; 44 = Dislike Slightly; 50 = Neither Like or Dislike; 56 = Like Slightly; 68 = Like Moderately; 78 = Like Very Much; 88 = Like Extremely; 100 = Greatest Imaginable Like
